messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the full paths are exactly the method-level values.
- The edit endpoint is annotated with
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}", method = RequestMethod.PUT)
  which makes PUT acceptable for that exact path.
- The delete endpoint is annotated with
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE)
  which makes DELETE acceptable for that exact path.
- There are no @RequestMapping entries for this exact path using GET, POST, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, or HEAD, and no mapping without an explicit method that would allow all methods. Therefore those methods are not acceptable based on the code.
- (Note: there are GET and POST mappings in this controller for the collection path /printshops/{id}/reviews, but those are different endpoints and do not affect /printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}.)
